  "prompt": "What does \u597d\u840c\u963f mean?",
  "response": "\"\u597d\u840c\u963f\" is a Chinese internet slang expression that can be roughly translated as:\n\n\"So cute!\" or \"How adorable!\"\n\nBreaking it down:\n- \u597d (h\u01ceo) means \"very\" or \"so\"\n- \u840c (m\u00e9ng) means \"cute\" or \"adorable\" (often used in internet/youth language)\n- \u963f (a) is a modal particle used to express emotion or emphasis\n\nThis phrase is commonly used in informal online communication, especially among young people, to express that something is extremely cute or endearing.",
